title: Woman, 1-year-old boy wounded in Shooting
content:
MILWAUKEE —
Two people -- including a 1-year-old boy -- were wounded in a Monday night shooting in Milwaukee, police said.
The pair were shot just before 9 p.m. in the 300 block of North Richards Street, near East Concordia Avenue. They were treated at a hospital, and their injuries were not considered life-threatening, police said.
No one was in custody as of 10 p.m., police said.
